<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer14293243748784352619">Jonathan Haidt is the Thomas Cooley Professor of Ethical Leadership at New York University&apos;s Stern School of Business. He is the author of The Righteous Mind: Why Good People Are Divided by Politics and Religion and The Happiness Hypothesis: Finding Modern Truth in Ancient Wisdom. He lives in New York City.</span>
  <span id="freeText14293243748784352619" style="display:none">Jonathan Haidt is the Thomas Cooley Professor of Ethical Leadership at New York University's Stern School of Business. He is the author of The Righteous Mind: Why Good People Are Divided by Politics and Religion and The Happiness Hypothesis: Finding Modern Truth in Ancient Wisdom. He lives in New York City.</span>
